<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.399478>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 8. General morphology of members of the ascid complex (all females, except 8, male): 1. Dorsal idiosoma of a Lasioseius (Blattisociidae) species; 2. Ventral idiosoma of a Lasioseius species; 3. Dorsal gnathosoma of a Lasioseius species; 4. Ventral gnathosoma of a Lasioseius species (a: palp trochanter; b: corniculus; c: internal malae; d: deutosternum; h 1, h 2, h 3: hypostomal setae; pc: palpcoxal seta); 5 – 8. Antiaxial view of chelicera. 5. Female Lasioseius species (a: dorsal seta; b: dorsal lyrifissure; c: pilus dentilis; d: antiaxial lyrifissure); 6. Female Proctolaelaps species, Melicharidae (a: lobe; b: ventral mucro; c: hyaline rim); 7. Female Mucroseius species, Melicharidae (a: distal mucro); 8. Male, Lasioseius species (a: spermatodactyl). Not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/399478/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.399496>
    dc:description "FIGURES 81 – 84. 81. Orolaelaps quisqualis De Leon, female, dorsal idiosoma; 82. O. quisqualis, female, ventral idiosoma (modified from Sourassou et al., 2015). 83. Spadiseius calyptrogynae Lindquist & Moraza, female, dorsal idiosoma; 84. S. calyptrogynae, female, ventral idiosoma (modified from Lindquist & Moraza, 2008). Scale bar = 100 Μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/399496/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.399482>
    dc:description "FIGURES 25 – 28. 25. Asca nelsoni Beard, Ochoa & Vega, female, dorsal idiosoma; 26. A. nelsoni, female, ventral idiosoma (modified from Beard et al., 2011). 27. Protogamasellus sigillophorus Mineiro, Lindquist & Moraes, female, dorsal idiosoma; 28. P. sigillophorus, female, ventral idiosoma (modified from Mineiro et al., 2009). Scale bar = 100 Μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/399482/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.399479>
    dc:description "FIGURES 9 – 16. General morphology of members of the ascid complex: 9. Phytoseiid-type sperm access system; 10. Laelapid-type sperm access system; 11. Pre-tarsus of a Lasioseius species; 12. Pre-tarsus of a Cheiroseius species; 13 – 16. Generalised legs, dorsal aspect. 13. Leg I; 14. Leg II, 15. Leg III; 16. Leg IV. Not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/399479/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.399480>
    dc:description "FIGURES 17 – 20. 17. Anephiasca latens Athias-Henriot, male, dorsal idiosoma; 18. Anephiasca affinis Athias-Henriot, female, ventral idiosoma (modified from Athias-Henriot, 1969 a). 19. Ectoantennoseius kitchingi Walter, female, dorsal idiosoma; 20. E. kitchingi, ventral idiosoma (modified from Walter, 1998). Scale bar = 100 Μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/399480/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.399481>
    dc:description "FIGURES 21 – 24. 21. Anystipalpus percicola Berlese, female, dorsal idiosoma; 22. A. percicola, female, ventral idiosoma (modified from Lindquist & Moraza, 2009). 23. Antennoseius (Vitzthumia) kamalii Moraza & Kazemi, female, dorsal idiosoma; 24. A. (V.) kamalii, female, ventral idiosoma (modified from Moraza & Kazemi, 2009). Scale bar = 100 Μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/399481/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.399483>
    dc:description "FIGURES 29 – 32. 29. Gamasellodes magniventris Mineiro, Lindquist & Moraes, female, dorsal idiosoma; 30. G. magniventris, female, ventral idiosoma (modified from Mineiro et al., 2009). 31. Iphidonopsis sculptus Gwiazdowicz, female, dorsal idiosoma; 32. I. sculptus, female, ventral idiosoma (modified from Gwiazdowicz, 2004). Scale bar = 100 Μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/399483/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.399484>
    dc:description "FIGURES 33 – 36. 33. Xenoseius elizae Halliday, Walter & Lindquist, female, dorsal idiosoma; 34. X. elizae, female, ventral idiosoma (modified from Halliday et al., 1998). 35. Zerconopsis pristis Halliday, Walter & Lindquist, female, dorsal idiosoma; 36. Z. pristis, female, ventral idiosoma (modified from Halliday et al., 1998). Scale bar = 100 Μm." ;
